comment: L'Hôpital's Rule for limits from the right. If ` F ` and ` G ` are differentiable real functions on ` ( A , B ) ` , and ` F ` and ` G ` both approach 0 at ` A ` , and ` G ( x ) ` and ` G ` ' ` ( x ) ` are not zero on ` ( A , B ) ` , and the limit of ` F ` ' ` ( x ) / G ` ' ` ( x ) ` at ` A ` is ` C ` , then the limit ` F ( x ) / G ( x ) ` at ` A ` also exists and equals ` C ` . (Contributed by Mario Carneiro, 29-Dec-2016.)
